<br>
Tanks seem to be atm the pawns of the battlefield, whose sole objective is to 'occupy' (I wont say &quot;kill&quot; as I'm not a very ambitious guy) the enemy casters, or protect the friendly ones, for 'the win'.<br>
<br>
As it is, we don't seem to get much in the way of RAs that let us do our job any better, unlike every other class, Bunker of Faith, Speed of Sound, etc, the horrendous MOC and all of these allow the receiving classes to do their job.... ultimately.<br>
<br>
Being a tank is all about chance more than anything else. There is nothing definite. Will you resist AOE stun? Wil you pop BT? Will that guy's slam miss you? Will Avoid Pain last out another 7 seconds? Will I crit for 99%? and now we have, is DT going to proc, will I parry? added to the list.<br>
<br>
I thought it was the casters who needed protection, but it looks as if the tank RAs are the ones to help us merely &quot;survive&quot;...<br>
<br>
As it is, when Mythic looks at RAs, I hope they give some serious thoguht to the tanks ones to make us really good at kiling our targets.<br>
<br>
And they'd better not be RAs that damn our brother tanks, like a &quot;you cant parry any more&quot; button. I'm talking about killing non-melee classes, primarily.<br>
